    <statement>
        <p>
Explain how to find the integral of <m>f(x)</m>.
        </p>
        <me>
f(x)=e^{\left(-\frac{1}{2} \, x\right)}.
        </me>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>
\int e^{\left(-\frac{1}{2} \, x\right)} dx=-2 \, e^{\left(-\frac{1}{2} \, x\right)}+C.
        </me>
    </answer>
